# Vertext Pay — Environment Variables Template
# Copy this to set your Netlify Environment Variables
# Go to: Netlify Dashboard > Your Site > Site Configuration > Environment Variables

# ── Supabase ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# From: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...your_anon_key...

# ── Paystack ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# From: Paystack Dashboard > Settings > API Keys & Webhooks
# PUBLIC key (safe to use in frontend)
PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_live_...

# SECRET key (server-side ONLY — goes into Supabase Edge Function secrets)
# DO NOT PUT THIS IN NETLIFY — set it in Supabase Edge Function secrets
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...

# Webhook secret (from Paystack Dashboard > Webhooks)
PAYSTACK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret

# ── How to set Supabase Edge Function secrets ─────────────────
# Run these commands in your terminal (after installing Supabase CLI):
#
#   supabase secrets set PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
#   supabase secrets set PAYSTACK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret
#
# The SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are automatically
# available to edge functions — no need to set those manually.

# ── Local development (.env.local) ───────────────────────────
# For local testing, create a .env.local file with:
# SUPABASE_URL=http://localhost:54321
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_local_anon_key
# PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_...  ← use TEST keys locally!
